First Financial Management Corp said itrevised the agreement under which it provides data processingservices to First Union Corp of Georgia &lt;FUNC>.    The company said the revised agreement establishes specificminimum payments to be made by First Union and shortens theduration of the original pact by 16 months, with the newagreement expiring on December 31, 1989.    Under terms of the amended contract, First Financial saidit received 19.8 mln dlrs in cash and is guaranteed anadditional 50.3 mln dlrs in service revenues.    The company said the agreement calls for minimum paymentsof 16.5 mln dlrs for the balance of 1987, 18 mln dlrs in 1988and 15.8 mln dlrs in 1989. Reuter&#3;